WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.996 align:middle line:90%
[WHOOSH]

00:00:01.996 --> 00:00:06.487 align:middle line:90%


00:00:06.487 --> 00:00:08.483 align:middle line:10%
[RAIN FALLING]

00:00:08.483 --> 00:00:14.970 align:middle line:90%


00:00:14.970 --> 00:00:15.990 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:15.990 --> 00:00:20.040 align:middle line:10%
>> It's mid-September, and
these Indian monsoon rains have

00:00:20.040 --> 00:00:21.870 align:middle line:10%
lasted a month
longer than usual.

00:00:21.870 --> 00:00:22.980 align:middle line:90%
[THUNDER CLAP]

00:00:22.980 --> 00:00:26.640 align:middle line:84%
It's not what I expected for
my second motorcycle journey

00:00:26.640 --> 00:00:29.060 align:middle line:90%
into the Himalayas with my guru.

00:00:29.060 --> 00:00:31.810 align:middle line:90%


00:00:31.810 --> 00:00:35.350 align:middle line:84%
On our first journey, I
didn't even know how to ride,

00:00:35.350 --> 00:00:37.510 align:middle line:90%
but faced the fear of death.

00:00:37.510 --> 00:00:39.880 align:middle line:90%
And I've come of age.

00:00:39.880 --> 00:00:42.100 align:middle line:84%
Now, together with
my teacher, we'll

00:00:42.100 --> 00:00:45.050 align:middle line:84%
take a group on what's
more than an adventure.

00:00:45.050 --> 00:00:46.510 align:middle line:90%
It's a pilgrimage.

00:00:46.510 --> 00:00:50.980 align:middle line:84%
Sheer cliffs, road killer
traffic, high altitude hiking,

00:00:50.980 --> 00:00:53.830 align:middle line:84%
all to reach four
sacred Himalayan peaks

00:00:53.830 --> 00:00:55.560 align:middle line:90%
in search of inner freedom.

00:00:55.560 --> 00:00:58.770 align:middle line:90%


00:00:58.770 --> 00:01:02.400 align:middle line:10%
But these monsoon rains have
been washing out villages,

00:01:02.400 --> 00:01:04.480 align:middle line:10%
destroying the
bridges and roads that

00:01:04.480 --> 00:01:07.810 align:middle line:10%
lead to the four sacred peaks.

00:01:07.810 --> 00:01:10.720 align:middle line:84%
But every adventure,
every pilgrimage

00:01:10.720 --> 00:01:12.760 align:middle line:84%
has its challenges,
especially when

00:01:12.760 --> 00:01:14.560 align:middle line:84%
we're seeking
something as precious

00:01:14.560 --> 00:01:16.145 align:middle line:90%
and elusive as freedom.

00:01:16.145 --> 00:01:24.170 align:middle line:90%


00:01:24.170 --> 00:01:26.720 align:middle line:84%
>> Whatever world we inhabit,
we start building myths

00:01:26.720 --> 00:01:30.020 align:middle line:84%
and symbols and start giving
meaning to things that they

00:01:30.020 --> 00:01:32.280 align:middle line:90%
don't have.

00:01:32.280 --> 00:01:37.070 align:middle line:84%
And it takes deep courage
to even pay attention to it.

00:01:37.070 --> 00:01:39.500 align:middle line:84%
How am I part of
a little bubble?

00:01:39.500 --> 00:01:42.430 align:middle line:84%
And how am I wasting my life
trying to maintain that bubble?

00:01:42.430 --> 00:01:47.620 align:middle line:90%


00:01:47.620 --> 00:01:51.980 align:middle line:84%
So one has to ask
oneself, why would I not

00:01:51.980 --> 00:01:55.270 align:middle line:84%
alter-- why would I not alter
this world that I inhabit?

00:01:55.270 --> 00:01:57.690 align:middle line:84%
Why would I not pop
out of this bubble?

00:01:57.690 --> 00:02:02.920 align:middle line:84%
How am I being enslaved
by the world I inhabit?

00:02:02.920 --> 00:02:05.980 align:middle line:84%
Am I the world or
the world is me?

00:02:05.980 --> 00:02:08.460 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:08.460 --> 00:02:14.412 align:middle line:90%


00:02:14.412 --> 00:02:15.404 align:middle line:90%
[HORN HONKS]

00:02:15.404 --> 00:02:17.884 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:17.884 --> 00:02:55.610 align:middle line:90%


00:02:55.610 --> 00:02:58.460 align:middle line:84%
This is not a journey
to feel better.

00:02:58.460 --> 00:02:59.630 align:middle line:90%
Do you understand?

00:02:59.630 --> 00:03:00.920 align:middle line:90%
You come here to transcend.

00:03:00.920 --> 00:03:08.300 align:middle line:90%


00:03:08.300 --> 00:03:10.760 align:middle line:90%
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

00:03:10.760 --> 00:03:12.236 align:middle line:90%


00:03:12.236 --> 00:03:14.696 align:middle line:10%
[MUSIC AND CHANTING]

00:03:14.696 --> 00:03:20.140 align:middle line:90%


00:03:20.140 --> 00:03:23.200 align:middle line:10%
>> The base camp for our
journey is Rishikesh, India,

00:03:23.200 --> 00:03:26.560 align:middle line:10%
where I've been coming yearly
for the last nine years.

00:03:26.560 --> 00:03:29.500 align:middle line:10%
I consider it my second
home, and the world

00:03:29.500 --> 00:03:33.130 align:middle line:10%
considers it the
birthplace of yoga.

00:03:33.130 --> 00:03:35.260 align:middle line:10%
We're nestled in the
foothills of the Himalayas

00:03:35.260 --> 00:03:40.480 align:middle line:10%
and right along the banks of
the holy and mighty Ganga River.

00:03:40.480 --> 00:03:43.960 align:middle line:10%
It's a place of
ashrams, of yogis,

00:03:43.960 --> 00:03:48.220 align:middle line:10%
that only in recent years, as
this bloom of yoga and spirit

00:03:48.220 --> 00:03:51.160 align:middle line:10%
has spread across
the world, has become

00:03:51.160 --> 00:03:56.140 align:middle line:10%
a bustling place of tourism, a
place of commerce, pilgrimage,

00:03:56.140 --> 00:04:00.385 align:middle line:10%
adventure, and a hotbed
for those seeking truth.

00:04:00.385 --> 00:04:02.524 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:04:02.524 --> 00:04:08.660 align:middle line:90%


00:04:08.660 --> 00:04:10.730 align:middle line:84%
When I come to
India, it's to study

00:04:10.730 --> 00:04:13.970 align:middle line:84%
with my teacher and our
leader on this pilgrimage,

00:04:13.970 --> 00:04:17.360 align:middle line:84%
Anand, who although
younger than I,

00:04:17.360 --> 00:04:20.209 align:middle line:84%
possesses the
wisdom of the sages.

00:04:20.209 --> 00:04:23.360 align:middle line:84%
He grew up here, on
the lap of his guru,

00:04:23.360 --> 00:04:26.780 align:middle line:84%
when Rishikesh was just
a small, small town.

00:04:26.780 --> 00:04:30.410 align:middle line:84%
Leopards, elephants,
deep jungle,

00:04:30.410 --> 00:04:34.260 align:middle line:84%
just the bells of the ashrams,
and rarely the sound of a car

00:04:34.260 --> 00:04:35.060 align:middle line:90%
or a honk.

00:04:35.060 --> 00:04:36.740 align:middle line:10%
[HORN HONKS]

00:04:36.740 --> 00:04:37.580 align:middle line:10%


00:04:37.580 --> 00:04:38.910 align:middle line:10%
>> Look at these mango trees.

00:04:38.910 --> 00:04:42.240 align:middle line:10%
I have to climb up here
and sleep sometimes.

00:04:42.240 --> 00:04:43.090 align:middle line:90%
Climb up on top.

00:04:43.090 --> 00:04:43.890 align:middle line:90%
>> You sleep?

00:04:43.890 --> 00:04:45.120 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, I sleep on the branch.

00:04:45.120 --> 00:04:45.930 align:middle line:90%
You've never done it?

00:04:45.930 --> 00:04:46.210 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

00:04:46.210 --> 00:04:47.310 align:middle line:90%
Do you hang something?

00:04:47.310 --> 00:04:48.180 align:middle line:90%
>> No, you sleep.

00:04:48.180 --> 00:04:50.730 align:middle line:84%
You go up and then
you let your legs hang

00:04:50.730 --> 00:04:52.869 align:middle line:84%
on one side and your
arms and you go to sleep.

00:04:52.869 --> 00:04:53.835 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:04:53.835 --> 00:04:55.520 align:middle line:10%
>> And so your chest
is on the branch?

00:04:55.520 --> 00:04:57.360 align:middle line:10%
>> Yeah, your chest
in on the branch.

00:04:57.360 --> 00:04:58.800 align:middle line:90%
Have you ever slept on a tree?

00:04:58.800 --> 00:05:00.510 align:middle line:90%
>> No, never.

00:05:00.510 --> 00:05:03.210 align:middle line:84%
In one sense, there's
this deep tradition,

00:05:03.210 --> 00:05:06.840 align:middle line:84%
walking with guru and student
on these paths that have been

00:05:06.840 --> 00:05:09.580 align:middle line:90%
walked for thousands of years.

00:05:09.580 --> 00:05:13.650 align:middle line:84%
But Anand has always been a
little more radical, modern,

00:05:13.650 --> 00:05:18.370 align:middle line:84%
adventurous, and some
might say even too risky.

00:05:18.370 --> 00:05:20.500 align:middle line:84%
He had a Vedic
prophecy that he'd die

00:05:20.500 --> 00:05:23.110 align:middle line:90%
in an accident in his late 20s.

00:05:23.110 --> 00:05:27.070 align:middle line:84%
But despite that, we rode
over the highest pass.

00:05:27.070 --> 00:05:31.480 align:middle line:84%
Some might also say that
I, too, am too risky.

00:05:31.480 --> 00:05:33.370 align:middle line:10%
Two years ago, I had
never ridden a bike

00:05:33.370 --> 00:05:36.700 align:middle line:10%
and went on a trip with
Anand and seven others

00:05:36.700 --> 00:05:39.340 align:middle line:10%
over the highest road in
the world, the highest pass.

00:05:39.340 --> 00:05:42.430 align:middle line:84%
And basically, learned how
to ride in India amidst

00:05:42.430 --> 00:05:44.380 align:middle line:84%
the altitudes, the
snows, and the traffic.

00:05:44.380 --> 00:05:46.745 align:middle line:90%


00:05:46.745 --> 00:05:48.870 align:middle line:84%
And for myself, I have this
passion and this desire

00:05:48.870 --> 00:05:51.900 align:middle line:84%
to transform, to walk
deep into the Himalayas,

00:05:51.900 --> 00:05:55.980 align:middle line:84%
to motorcycle again through this
adventurous traffic and cliffs

00:05:55.980 --> 00:06:00.330 align:middle line:84%
and see what is just inside me
that is dying, dying to die.

00:06:00.330 --> 00:06:01.710 align:middle line:90%
Dying to crack open.

00:06:01.710 --> 00:06:06.000 align:middle line:84%
What part of me wants
to relinquish and show

00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:09.330 align:middle line:84%
the light that has
been saying, hey, hey.

00:06:09.330 --> 00:06:10.660 align:middle line:90%
What about me?

00:06:10.660 --> 00:06:11.796 align:middle line:90%
This is who I am, yeah?

00:06:11.796 --> 00:06:14.276 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:06:14.276 --> 00:06:17.750 align:middle line:90%


00:06:17.750 --> 00:06:19.700 align:middle line:84%
The eight riders
and eight passengers

00:06:19.700 --> 00:06:21.770 align:middle line:90%
will arrive tomorrow.

00:06:21.770 --> 00:06:24.932 align:middle line:84%
Most are new to India,
to Anand, and some

00:06:24.932 --> 00:06:25.890 align:middle line:90%
are even new to riding.

00:06:25.890 --> 00:06:28.630 align:middle line:90%


00:06:28.630 --> 00:06:31.323 align:middle line:84%
They'll get the exact
trip details when we meet,

00:06:31.323 --> 00:06:32.990 align:middle line:84%
but they all know
we're in for something

00:06:32.990 --> 00:06:36.230 align:middle line:84%
more than a yoga class,
more than a wisdom talk,

00:06:36.230 --> 00:06:38.730 align:middle line:84%
and more than a
motorcycle adventure.

00:06:38.730 --> 00:06:42.170 align:middle line:84%
It's a real quest to
four sacred sites that

00:06:42.170 --> 00:06:47.060 align:middle line:84%
will each reveal to us
aspects of freedom, Kedarnath,

00:06:47.060 --> 00:06:52.230 align:middle line:84%
Tungnath, Badrinath, and Hemkund
Sahib and its Hidden Valley

00:06:52.230 --> 00:06:55.050 align:middle line:90%
of the Flowers.

00:06:55.050 --> 00:06:58.800 align:middle line:84%
We get there through a mix of
road killer motorcycle traffic,

00:06:58.800 --> 00:07:02.760 align:middle line:84%
washed out roads, high
altitude hiking, all while

00:07:02.760 --> 00:07:05.070 align:middle line:90%
being pushed by a guru.

00:07:05.070 --> 00:07:09.000 align:middle line:84%
Pushed to go inside
and pushed to go deep,

00:07:09.000 --> 00:07:12.500 align:middle line:84%
so it's fitting that this
pilgrimage begins here

00:07:12.500 --> 00:07:16.490 align:middle line:84%
at the deep and powerful
Himalayan-fed Ganga River.

00:07:16.490 --> 00:07:19.820 align:middle line:84%
